items.title: FTP Unencrypted Cleartext Login

details.Impact: [[markup]]An attacker can uncover login names and passwords by sniffing traffic to the   FTP service.
details.Detection: [[markup]]Tries to login to a non FTPS enabled FTP service without sending a   'AUTH TLS' command first and checks if the service is accepting the login without enforcing the use of   the 'AUTH TLS' command.
details.Technical Details:
The remote FTP service accepts logins without a previous sent 'AUTH TLS' command. Response(s):

Anonymous sessions:     331 Password required for anonymous.
Non-anonymous sessions: 331 Password required for appcheck-ng-vt.

items.description:
The remote host is running a FTP service that allows cleartext logins over
  unencrypted connections.
items.solution: [[markup]]Enable FTPS or enforce the connection via the 'AUTH TLS' command. Please see   the manual of the FTP service for more information.
items.synopsis:
The remote host is running a FTP service that allows cleartext logins over
  unencrypted connections.

items.title: Apache Tomcat < v9.0.0.M10 - External Control of Assumed-Immutable Web Parameter in JSP Servlet (CVE-2016-6796)

details.Technical Details: [[markup]]This vulnerability was detected by comparing the detected version (8.0.32) against the affected versions reported by the vendor.

items.description:
[[markup]]

**Product Background**

**Apache Tomcat** is a free and open-source Java web application server. It provides a "pure Java" HTTP web server environment in which Java code can also run, implementing the Jakarta Servlet, Jakarta Expression Language, and WebSocket technologies. Tomcat is released with **Catalina** (a servlet and JSP Java Server Pages container), **Coyote** (an HTTP connector), **Coyote JK** (JK protocol proxy connector) and **Jasper** (a JSP engine). Tomcat can optionally be bundled with Java Enterprise Edition (Jakarta EE) as **Apache TomEE** to deliver a complete application server with enterprise features such as distributed computing and web services.

**Vulnerability Summary**

A malicious web application running on Apache Tomcat 9.0.0.M1 to 9.0.0.M9, 8.5.0 to 8.5.4, 8.0.0.RC1 to 8.0.36, 7.0.0 to 7.0.70 and 6.0.0 to 6.0.45 was able to bypass a configured SecurityManager via manipulation of the configuration parameters for the JSP Servlet.

**References**

2017.name: A5-Broken Access Control
2017.description: Restrictions on what authenticated users are allowed to do are often not properly enforced. Attackers can exploit these flaws to access unauthorized functionality and/or data, such as access other users' accounts, view sensitive files, modify other users' data, change access rights, etc

2021.name: A01:2021 - Broken Access Control
2021.description: Access control enforces policy such that users cannot act outside of their intended permissions. Failures typically lead to unauthorized information disclosure, modification, or destruction of all data or performing a business function outside the user's limits.

items.title: SSL/TLS: Report Vulnerable Cipher Suites for HTTPS

details.Technical Details:
::

    'Vulnerable' cipher suites accepted by this service via the TLSv1.2 protocol:
    
    TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA (SWEET32)
    TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA (SWEET32)
details.External Sources:
[[markup]]The following external sources can help provide some more information on this vulnerability

 * [[https://bettercrypto.org/]]
 * [[https://mozilla.github.io/server-side-tls/ssl-config-generator/]]
 * [[https://sweet32.info/]]
details.CVEs:
[[markup]]This vulnerability covers the following CVEs:

 * CVE-2016-2183
 * CVE-2016-6329
 * CVE-2020-12872

items.description:
[[markup]]This routine reports all SSL/TLS cipher suites accepted by a service   where attack vectors exists only on HTTPS services.

These rules are applied for the evaluation of the vulnerable cipher suites:

- 64-bit block cipher 3DES vulnerable to the SWEET32 attack (CVE-2016-2183).
items.solution:
[[markup]]The configuration of this services should be changed so   that it does not accept the listed cipher suites anymore.

Please see the references for more resources supporting you with this task.
items.synopsis: [[markup]]This routine reports all SSL/TLS cipher suites accepted by a service   where attack vectors exists only on HTTPS services.

items.title: Possible Scan Turbulence: Gateway Timeout/Error Detected

details.Technical Details: [[markup]]The server returned a **Web server is down** HTTP status indicating that the remote system is experiencing technical difficulties. However, another request to **https://example.x73zjffz.com/** did not return the same code (**200** was returned) and therefore this error may only affect a specific route and/or could becaused by a specific security check.

items.description:
[[markup]]The server responded with a HTTP status code that may indicate that the remote server is experiencing technical
difficulties that are likely to affect the scan and may also be affecting other application users.
items.solution:
[[markup]]Review the affected target to determine the reason it is returning a gateway error code. Reducing scan threads
may help alleviate the problem.
